/* The breathing oscillation modulates the field amplitude:
   د†_a(x,t) = [A_a(r) + خµ_a(r)sin(د‰_b t)] أ— cos(kz + خ´_a)

   The triple product becomes:
   P(t) = [Aâ‚€ + خµâ‚€ sin(د‰t)] أ— [Aâ‚پ + خµâ‚پ sin(د‰t)] أ— [Aâ‚‚ + خµâ‚‚ sin(د‰t)] أ— cosآ³(...)

   Expanding to leading order in خµ:
   P(t) â‰ˆ Aâ‚€Aâ‚پAâ‚‚ [1 + sin(د‰t)(خµâ‚€/Aâ‚€ + خµâ‚پ/Aâ‚پ + خµâ‚‚/Aâ‚‚)] أ— cosآ³(...)

   The V(P) potential creates an effective coupling between the breathing
   modes of nearby baryons through the cross-term in P_total = Pâ‚پ + Pâ‚‚. */

print("Breathing mode perturbation: د† â†’ A(r)[1 + خµ sin(د‰t)]");
