/* For two baryons at separation D, breathing at the SAME frequency د‰
   but with phases دˆâ‚پ and دˆâ‚‚:

   Pâ‚پ(t) = Pâ‚€ [1 + 3خµ sin(د‰t + دˆâ‚پ)]
   Pâ‚‚(t) = Pâ‚€ [1 + 3خµ sin(د‰t + دˆâ‚‚)]

   In the overlap region: P_total = Pâ‚پ + Pâ‚‚ (approximate for small overlap)
   V(P_total) = V(Pâ‚پ + Pâ‚‚)

   The interaction energy comes from the cross-term:
   V(Pâ‚پ+Pâ‚‚) - V(Pâ‚پ) - V(Pâ‚‚) â‰ˆ V''(0) أ— Pâ‚پ أ— Pâ‚‚

   (This is the Born approximation for weak overlap.)

   Time-averaged interaction:
   âں¨Pâ‚پ Pâ‚‚âں©_t = Pâ‚€آ² [1 + 9خµآ² âں¨sin(د‰t+دˆâ‚پ)sin(د‰t+دˆâ‚‚)âں©]
              = Pâ‚€آ² [1 + (9خµآ²/2) cos(دˆâ‚پ-دˆâ‚‚)]

   The cos(دˆâ‚پ-دˆâ‚‚) term IS the Adler synchronization coupling!
   When دˆâ‚پ=دˆâ‚‚ (in-phase): âں¨Pâ‚پPâ‚‚âں© is maximized â†’ V_int most negative
   When دˆâ‚پ=دˆâ‚‚+د€ (anti-phase): âں¨Pâ‚پPâ‚‚âں© is minimized â†’ V_int less negative */

print("");
print("Time-averaged breathing cross-term:");
